# Krexion repository line-ending & encoding policy.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
# We had a fatal customer-side install failure where install-master.ps1
# was committed without a UTF-8 BOM and contained em-dashes (—). On
# Windows PowerShell 5.1 (the default on every Windows 10/11 install),
# a BOM-less script is parsed as Windows-1252 ANSI, so the UTF-8 bytes
# `E2 80 94` for `—` were misread as `â€"` — which immediately breaks
# string quoting and crashes the customer's installer with
# "Unexpected token 'will'" / "Missing closing ')' in expression".
#
# These rules pin the canonical form so neither git auto-conversion
# nor a future editor can ever re-introduce that class of bug.

# ── Default: text files normalise to LF on commit, native on checkout
*           text=auto

# ── Windows installer payload: SHIPPED files (downloaded by customers,
#    extracted on Windows, executed by cmd.exe / PowerShell). Must be
#    CRLF + appropriate encoding so they work on any Windows locale.
Krexion-User-Package/*.bat   text eol=crlf working-tree-encoding=ASCII
Krexion-User-Package/*.ps1   text eol=crlf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8
Krexion-User-Package/*.txt   text eol=crlf working-tree-encoding=ASCII

# Same rules for the standalone master script at repo root
install-master.ps1           text eol=crlf working-tree-encoding=UTF-8

# Anything else PowerShell-flavoured anywhere in the tree
*.ps1                        text eol=crlf
*.psm1                       text eol=crlf
*.psd1                       text eol=crlf

# Windows batch / cmd: always CRLF, always ASCII (cmd.exe chokes on BOM)
*.bat                        text eol=crlf
*.cmd                        text eol=crlf

# Shell scripts & makefiles: LF only (anything else breaks bash)
*.sh                         text eol=lf
*.bash                       text eol=lf
Makefile                     text eol=lf
makefile                     text eol=lf

# Docker / yaml / config files: LF
Dockerfile                   text eol=lf
*.yml                        text eol=lf
*.yaml                       text eol=lf

# ── Binary types: never touch ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Customer-facing diagnostic .bat — declared binary so git stores the
# CRLF bytes verbatim. Without this, GitHub raw URL serves LF-only and
# cmd.exe silently fails on the first line.
installer/Krexion-Diagnostic.bat   binary
*.png                        binary
*.jpg                        binary
*.jpeg                       binary
*.gif                        binary
*.ico                        binary
*.zip                        binary
*.exe                        binary
*.dll                        binary
*.pdf                        binary
*.woff                       binary
*.woff2                      binary
*.ttf                        binary
*.eot                        binary
*.mp3                        binary
*.mp4                        binary
